programme.title: The Boys from Brooklyn (1952)
programme.desc: Duke Mitchell and Sammy Petrillo, a pair who made a brief career out of being dead ringers for Dean Martin and Jerry Lewis, play a couple of Brooklyn chumps stranded on the Pacific island of Cola-Cola where a mad scientist (Bela Lugosi) is conducting some hair-raising experiments. This oddity was also released as Bela Lugosi Meets A Brooklyn Gorilla, but no matter what you call it, this is a horror film that will stiffen you with laughter! Also, look for the great Ray ‘Crash’ Corrigan in the gorilla suit…

programme.title: Bowery at Midnight
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi is a college professor by day and runs a soup kitchen and hospital by night in New York City's Bowery section - but it's just a front for more sinister activities. When things get out of hand, Lugosi kills his henchmen, who wind up as zombies in the cellar. Director Wallace Fox, who had already worked with Lugosi on two previous Monogram films, Spooks Run Wild and The Corpse Vanishes, comes through with a true horror gem.

programme.title: White Zombie (1932)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: The Corpse Vanishes
programme.desc: Horror to make your hair stand on end! Another Monogram Pictures horror classic starring the inimitable Bela Lugosi, The Corpse Vanishes is an eerie, unsettling mystery about a mad scientist (Lugosi) who injects his aging wife with fluids from virginal young brides in order to preserve her beauty. Noted as one of the most successful and imitated collaborations between Monogram and Lugosi, this film’s plot bears an uncanny resemblance to the real world story of the murderous Elizabeth Bathory.

programme.title: Scared To Death
programme.desc: The only color film to star Bela Lugosi was this mystery thriller from director Christy Cabanne (The Mummy’s Hand) made for the short­lived Golden Gate Pictures during the early months of 1946. Lugosi plays Professor Leonide, a cagy character who may have had something to do with the death of a young woman (who happens to be telling her tale from a slab at the morgue!). George Zucco, Molly Lamont, and Joyce Compton also star, as well as Angelo Rossitto, (Freaks) as a menacing dwarf with a habit of stepping on Lugosi’s foot!

programme.title: Chandu on the Magic Island
programme.desc: A cult practices human sacrifices to resurrect the spirit of an ancient goddess in this installment of the Chandu series. Bela Lugosi stars, along with Maria Alba as Princess Nadji. The movie was culled from a 12-part serial, The Return of Chandu.

programme.title: The Death Kiss (1932)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi was fresh off the success of Dracula when he appeared in this low-budget murder mystery for director Edwin L. Marin (Tall in the Saddle, The Invisible Agent) It’s set in the world of movies, where an actor is killed during a production. Having been involved with most of the women connected with the studio, there are plenty of suspects! Along with Lugosi the cast includes David Manners, Adrienne Ames, and John Wray.

programme.desc: "Carnival of Souls" is the story of a young woman who goes along for the ride when two hot-rodders hold a drag race and are forced off a bridge, plunging into the flooded river below. The sole survivor of the accident, Mary, accepts a job in a new town as a church organist where she is repeatedly troubled by visions of a nearby abandoned carnival and a smiling white-faced man with dark rimmed eyes. One of the most atmospherically eerie works of American horror cinema, the film garnered a significant cult following years after being released in 1962, and is essential for every horror collection.

Directed by horror aficionado Frank R. Strayer and produced independently, this film bears many of the hallmarks of a Universal prestige picture, and was a rarity for its time, considering its relatively sympathetic treatment of vampires.

As his paranoid feelings increase, Chet decides to create some mayhem of his own, including arson! A cast of unknowns come together for this feature by Boris Petroff, who also directed the cult favorite, The Unearthly. Just sit back and enjoy watching poor Chet lose touch with reality!

programme.title: Dean's Place

programme.title: The Deadly Companions

Marking the feature film debut of one of Hollywood’s most influential and widely referenced auteur directors, Sam Peckinpah, The Deadly Companions centers on a redemptive journey to escort a funeral procession through dangerous Indian Territory. Featuring fine work from a top-notch cast that includes the inimitable Maureen O’Hara at the height of her illustrious career, Peckinpah’s first foray into film provides a promising glance into the energetic and violent nature of his iconic later works.

programme.title: Captain Scarlett

The Duke of Corlais (Manolo Fabregas) has begun persecuting people, while a lovely princess is trying to escape an arranged marriage to an evil count (Eduardo Noriega). programme.title: Cupid and Valentine's Day
programme.desc: Each year on February 14, love is celebrated all across the globe. Valentine's Day, also known as Saint Valentine's Day or the Feast of Saint Valentine, wasn't always just greetings, candy and flowers. The early days of this festivity are mired in legend and lore. From the imprisonment of Saint Valentine of Rome for preaching to Christians, to the many legend of this saint's healing powers. Let's trace the story back to its origins. Where did this ancient tradition begin? And how does Cupid come into the picture? We're going to answer these questions and many more in our in-depth look at Cupid! And Valentine's Day!

programme.title: Dating My Mother
programme.desc: Unemployed and living in his New Jersey hometown, brash screenwriter Danny spends his days practicing yoga, sipping red wine, and power-walking with his mother Joan. But when she reveals she’s seeing another man, their version of domestic bliss comes crashing down. DATING MY MOTHER follows the intimate and tumultuous relationship between a single mother and her gay son as they navigate the dizzying world of online dating. While they search for their versions of Mr. Right, mother and son discover that sometimes you need to be apart in order to grow together.

programme.title: Jobriath A.D.
programme.desc: Known as the first openly gay rock star, Jobriath’s reign was a brief two years. Done in by over-hyped publicity, shunned by the gay community, and dismissed by critics, Jobriath retreated to the Chelsea Hotel, where he died forgotten, one of the earliest casualties of AIDS. But years later, new fans discover his music, and acts such as The Pet Shop Boys, Def Leppard, and Morrissey cite him as an influence. Experience the heartbreaking, unbelievable story of the one, the only, Jobriath.

programme.title: Amplify Voices

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: Being Queer In The Country/Defying What's Blackness, What's Femininity And What's Masculinity/Drag Culture Really Does Have A Place In Society/Football, Family And Coming Out/I Am A UFO Child That Was Left Here By Mistake/I Had To Ditch The Trans Narrative And Finally Start Writing My Own/I Promised Myself I Would Never Bully Again/Ian McKellen Would Be Proud Of Me/I'm Black, Jewish, But Guess What? I'm Also Gay/ I'm Christian But I'm Also A Very Out Lesbian S1 E11-20 | Rachel grew up in a small West Virginia town. After living in other larger cities she learns the importance of letting "country queers" know that it's okay to stay in rural towns. One group of people told Icon to "act like a man." Another group told him to "femme it up" and to be a "big black girl" and to "snap, snap, snap and be sassy." Icon decided to ignore them all and just be Icon. When Vincent Cooper first saw a drag queen, he was physically repulsed. Over the years, he learned to not only embrace them but view them as an important part of society. Robbie comes out to his mom in the middle of her beloved Seattle Seahawks football game. And some things just have to wait till commercial. Cecilia Gentili's brother told her she was an alien. Being transgender, she thought it might be true. After watching "Priscilla Queen of the Desert", Kathryn Gonzales learned what "transgender" meant. After attempting unsuccessfully to transition five times, Kathryn had an epiphany at a stop light and finally found her own path. After making derogatory comments about a gay classmate, Joseph's friend tells him something that changes him forever. When Adam Sandel first moved to San Francisco, he had the pleasure of interviewing out and proud actor Sir Ian McKellen, who gave Adam some advice that changed his life.Jason Daniel Fair has a white, Jewish mother and a black, Christian dad. His dad gave him advice as a child that helped him embrace his differences and shaped who he is as a gay man. Crystal Cheatham was told by her church that she had the voice, an incredible gift of playing the guitar, the ability to lead a band, to write music, and to mentor children. But all that meant nothing to them because she's a "practicing homosexual."

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Savannah is a ray of light in the LGBTQ+ youth community and she wants to be a Disney animator one day. She is a member of the Mormon church and has been all of her life however when Savannah came out to her to ward during a sacrament meeting a year ago, the Bishop had her microphone turned off, stopping her right before she had wrapped up her speech. She has since become an advocate for LGBTQ+ teens.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cody (Elton Cray) is a professional musician & rapper. We did an initial interview with him in his home, then visited with him almost 10 months later at one of his shows. An interesting and passionate man who speaks his mind, Cody's music is about his struggles with himself and others around him who have been indifferent to how he identifies.

programme.title: Hank
programme.desc: After reluctantly agreeing to an open relationship, middle aged gay man Hank starts a wild journey with a mysterious young man only to find he’s put himself in danger. Narrowly escaping with just his life, and forced to walk home alone and naked in the middle of the night, Hank realizes the compromise he made to save his marriage has gone too far.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: Still I Strive
programme.desc: The NACA orphanage in Phnom Penh, work to achieve one of the highest honors in Cambodian society, to perform before the Princess Bopha Devi. The children's epic performance is recreated as a cinematic adventure that parallels their harrowing backstories.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: Happy Playland
programme.desc: S1 E1-5 | Billie Haare, an anxious actress caught between her passion for stage and her parents’ dreams of the silver screens, starts a new job at a desolate indoor playground, managed by wannabe-insta-star Cris. Billie quickly develops feelings for social justice warrior, Zara, who is sadly 23 and not looking for anything serious. After a passionate moment in the ball pit, Billie and Zara both begin to question what they want. But the playland is soon to be closed - and Billie’s anxiety can only handle so much. Cris decides to intervene. Can Billie woo Zara into forever and always? Will anyone ned up happy? Will Cris’ trip to Queenstown increase her followers? Only time will tell, in the place where dreams come true, Happy Playland, The Wellington branch.

programme.title: A Queer City
programme.desc: Three young drag artists navigate the rising drag scene in Norwich.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: The Billionaire
programme.desc: A gender-swapped independent film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's classic play 'The Millionairess', transposed into a contemporary context of Gay Marriage and Asexuality, THE BILLIONAIRE follows a haughty and prudish young billionaire's quest for love, despite all the odds. The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: Becoming Queen
programme.desc: There has never been a band like Queen, and there never will again. Take a twenty year ride with the people who knew them best.

programme.title: Memories Of A Penitent Heart
programme.desc: Combining a wealth of recently discovered home movies, video, and written documents with artfully shot contemporary interviews and vérité footage, Memories Of A Penitent Heart is a documentary that cracks open a Pandora’s box of unresolved family drama. Originating from filmmaker Cecilia Aldarondo’s suspicion that there was something ugly in her family’s past, the film charts her excavation of the buried family conflict around her uncle Miguel’s death, and her search for Miguel’s partner Robert a generation later. After two years of dead ends, Robert turns up: but he’s not the same man. He’s reinvented himself as Father Aquin, a Franciscan monk with twenty-five years of pent-up grief and bitterness. For the first time, a member of Miguel’s family wants to hear Aquin’s side of the story—but is it too little, too late? ​A story about the mistakes of the past and the second chances of the present, Memories Of A Penitent Heart is a cautionary tale about the unresolved conflicts wrought by AIDS, and a nuanced exploration of how faith is used and abused in times of crisis.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Between The Shades
programme.desc: A look into what labels a life in current LGBT America. Fifty conversations exploring the many different shades of being “gay” in America. This conversation focuses on the degrees and varying perceptions about how people define themselves, their lives, struggles and triumphs.

programme.title: Happy Birthday Marsha
programme.desc: Happy Birthday, Marsha! is a film about iconic transgender artist and activist, Marsha "Pay it No Mind" Johnson, and her life in the hours before she ignited the 1969 Stonewall Riots in New York City.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E3-4 | Lucy visits the Gay Straight Alliance to gain support for Gay Prom Royalty. She shares some personal secrets to old and new friends. Anita’s throwing a party and a surprise promposal! Lucy has social anxiety about it.

programme.title: Ava's Impossible Things
programme.desc: Ava and her mother Claire are bonded by many things...unconditional love, a passion for the arts, a belief that magic exists, and an insidious disease that will one day end both their lives. It's been three years since Ava moved back into her mother's house to care for Claire, and as Ava witnesses the slow downward spiral all she can do is keep her mother's spirits up while locking away the fears of her own future. Today is a day like any other until rare guests and unexpected events compel Claire to make a shocking announcement, sending Ava into a tailspin. Unable to deal with reality, Ava cries herself to sleep in her mother's arms and escapes to a dream world filled with old friends and long forgotten desires.

programme.title: Chicken with Chef Caroline McCann

programme.title: Fast Favs

programme.title: Fruit

programme.title: Red curry from scratch

programme.title: Kale and Kumquats

programme.title: Demystifying Indian Food

programme.title: XYZ Science & Tech Spotlight - Terpenes
programme.desc: Terpenes play a critical role in cannabis - but what exactly are they? How do they affect our bodies, and what changes do they engender in us when we consume them? Join us as we put on our lab coats and visit Cannalysis Lead Specialist Christina Sheehan to find out more about these fascinating chemicals, their health benefits, and how one company is leading the world in terpene analysis and testing.

programme.title: Canada Cultivation and Mushroom Editing
programme.desc: In early May, we had Mydecine (NEO: MYCO) (OTCMKTS: MYCOF) CSO Rob Roscow on the Dales Report to talk about their 2a clinical trials. Today we have Damon Michaels with us to discuss some of the recent news that’s come out for Mydecine including Health Canada’s approval of the expansion of their cultivation facilities here in Canada. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Canadian expansion means that Mydecine has “instant access” and allows them to supply clinical trials says Michaels - - The possibility of editing mushrooms - - Mydecine facility in Canada probably won’t scale to meet a commercial need, says Michaels - - The roadmap for the next 12 months? Proving efficacy and safety – and looking at protocols

programme.title: The Dales Report
programme.desc: Setting up to manufacture synthetic psychedelics is fairly expensive. Unsurprisingly, many companies in the space have opted to put their money, so to speak, on one or two horses as a result. PharmAla Biotech is a new Canadian psychedelics manufacturing company. Their focus is manufacturing MDMA and other MDXX substances. We’re thrilled to have the CEO of PharmAla, Nick Kadysh, with us on this episode of The Dales Report. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Kadysh had a strong background in running regulatory departments for large corporations before he launched PharmAla - - PharmAla Biotech’s focus and how Kadysh feels they bring a unique proposition - - Why MDMA? - - Investors “more sophisticated” says Kadysh

programme.title: Science & Tech Spotlight: Counterfeit Cannabis
programme.desc: As the legal cannabis market grows, so does the opportunity for crime. The cannabis market is currently being infiltrated by counterfeit products that purport to be from popular brands, but can in fact carry a dangerous -- sometimes deadly risk. Cannalysis CEO Tyler Autera walks us through the legal testing process and shows how his company is protecting consumers against dangerous, fraudulent products.

programme.desc: Certification for sustainable, naturally-grown agriculture, Clean Green Certified is the closest to “Organic” that the cannabiz can get. We're honored to welcome founder Chris Van Hook. Together, we explore the value of certification for industry operators, consumers and the planet. programme.title: Meet the International Canna Farmer's Association Chair, Kristin Nevedal
programme.desc: We're honored to welcome to today's show, Kristin Nevedal, International Cannabis Farmer's Association Chair. The International Cannabis Farmer’s Association strives to empower traditional Cannabis farmers through education, research and advocacy. Their programs raise public awareness about the benefits of traditionally farmed Cannabis and provide educational resources for farmers, regulators, industry and consumers. They advocate for the development of responsible regulations in CA, which are seen as crucially important due to the state’s significance to national and international policy development. They will promote public policy that ensures an equal share of licenses are issued to traditional sun grown Cannabis farmers. They conduct research to quantify the ecological superiority of traditionally farmed Cannabis as well as gathering data necessary to establish internationally recognized appellations of origin. They create a dynamic and creative consumer direct educational campaign that highlights the quality and ecological superiority of traditionally farmed sun grown Cannabis.

programme.title: What's It Like to Judge The Emerald Cup - Go Backstage with Swami Select
programme.desc: Founded in 2003, Northern California’s Emerald Cup advances the concept of sustainable, outdoor farming of medical cannabis. Longtime advocates of the spiritually and physically healing potential of regeneratively-grown cannabis, Swami Select founders Nikki Lastreto and Swami Chaitanya have judged The Emerald Cup’s flower competition since the event began. As the largest, organic, outdoor, medicinal cannabis competition in the world, The Cup advances our movement by cross-pollinating cultivators, patients and patrons with scientific and agriculture experts who work across industries. Now a global movement, the community celebration honors the year’s best, sun-grown, medicinal cannabis producers.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Alonzo Bodden
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is standup comedian and former “Last Comic Standing” champion Alonzo Bodden. DL and Alonzo discuss the issues of the pandemic and working as entertainers. They also discuss politics, racism, and other issues in the black community.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Lee Merritt
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is attorney Lee Merritt, who is the family attorney for Ahmaud Arbery. Arbery is a young, 25 year old black man from Georgia who was killed in February after being chased by two armed white men who told police he looked like a burglary suspect. Merritt shared the video Tuesday afternoon and said Arbery’s family was forced to watch for the first time online.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Nate Burleson
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former NFL star Nate Burleson. Nate played for 11 years in the NFL, and is now the host of “Good Morning Football” on the NFL Network. Nate also is a host on the “NFL Today” on CBS. Nate discusses the continuing issues of race in the NFL, and the implications in society as a whole.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tamika Mallory
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Flavor Flav
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is rapper and tv personality Flavor Flav. Flav was an original member of the ground-breaking rap group Public Enemy. DL and Flav discuss the origins of Public Enemy music and the importance of it today. Flav also shares his thoughts on politics and how it affects people.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Devon Franklin
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is producer, motivational speaker, and best selling author Devon Franklin. Devon shares his perspective on a variety of issues like the global pandemic, police killings of black men, and how faith plays an important role in everyday lives.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor & Comedian Aries Spear
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor comedian Aries Spears. From TV to film, actor Aries Spears spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about recent issues with Mike Epps and a social media post about black on black crime versus police racism against blacks.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

Also, launch of Blue Origin's NS17, with its own cargo of NASA research and well as international artwork!

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Louisville
programme.desc: And we are off! We learn the history of the world famous Kentucky Derby, and call our shot, at one of America's most famous brands, Louisville Slugger. Also, we zip line in the world's only underground zip line attraction, and learn about Muhammad Ali's legacy at the Ali Center.

programme.title: Oslo
programme.desc: Set sail to Oslo, Norway. Climb the fort walls at Akershus Fortress and discover the North and South Poles at the Fram Museum. Then, unearth ancient Viking ship treasures at the Viking Ship Museum, and we will brave the open waters of the Pacific with Thor Heyerdahl at the Kon-tiki museum.

programme.title: Chile - Desert Voices
programme.desc: Known as the driest desert on Earth, the Atacama stretches 1,500 miles along the Andes Cordillera and attracts visitors from all over the world. The intense drought this region experiences helps preserve archaeological sites and geologic features dating back to the origins of the Likan Antai people.

programme.title: Sri Lanka - The Emerald Isle
programme.desc: Sri Lanka is principally known for its heavenly beaches, bold-green mountains and forests, its glorious waterfalls, and renowned tea plantations. It has begun to preserve its ecological resources, and respect the environment more and more, so that everyone may enjoy the land's bounty over time.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: Alberta, Canada
programme.desc: In Alberta, Canada, Donna’s first impression is- snow. And she enjoys it to the fullest. Donna finds myriad ways of taking advantage of a snowy environment, including snow-biking, ice walking, and staying at a world-renowned resort.

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Chinguetti
programme.desc: Once at a crossroads of ancient trade routes, the ksar of Chinguetti, Mauritania exists like a pearl in the desert on the western edge of the Sahara Desert, a force of nature whose sand reaches every crook and crevice of life in this land.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Tabriz, Capital of Merchants
programme.desc: Enter the city that once was the core of the entire Silk Road in Persia: Tabriz, Iran. Find your way into the city’s bazaar, the finest in the country, and wander through its 22-mile labyrinth. Also, meet Dr. Faribouz Esmaeli, the heart of this architectural gem, who oversaw its restoration.

programme.title: Venice, Gateway to the Orient
programme.desc: Just like Marco Polo ages ago, we begin in Venice, Italy. On our journey, we will witness mosaics of St. Mark’s Basilica that reveal links connecting Venice with distant lands in Asia. We will taste Venetian cuisine, and visit an Armenian monastery packed with manuscripts written in all languages.

programme.title: Bosphorus, Astride Two Worlds
programme.desc: At the edge of the European continent, Alfred de Montesquiou enters Turkish territory through the city of Edirne to discover Ottoman architectural wonders and the traditional local sport of oil-wrestling in which men are doused in olive oil before each bout.

programme.title: Of Kings and Gods: The Skyros Horse
programme.desc: This is the story of a mighty horse of legend. The Skyros Horses of Greece are found not only in its hills and plains, but also in its famous monuments such as the Parthenon. For thousands of years the Skyros horse has stood alongside heroes in battle and survives to this day as a Greek treasure.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Down Under: The Wild West of Cooking
programme.desc: Melbourne, Australia boasts hard-living, good-natured, and eccentric lovers of food - Tony's kind of people. In search of the outlaws of food, Tony explores a pasteurization-free cheese factory, and an old-world cured jamon workshop.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: Kyoto, Japan
programme.desc: The spiritual heart of Japan, Kyoto offers a glimpse of Japanese life as it used to be, primarily because it was spared during World War II. Comfortable streets with wooden homes, impressive temples, and a dedication to ancient Japanese traditions make Kyoto one of Japan's most visited cities.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: The Route of the Two Oceans
programme.desc: The thin ridge that links the two Americas is a miniature world unto itself and concentrates a vast amount of diversity into a small area of land. Follow the Inter-American Highway from Panama City to the Isthmus of Rivas in Nicaragua, the narrowest ridge of Central America.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: New Orleans
programme.desc: The saints come marching in as we tour the New Orlean's iconic St. Louis Cathedral and the mysterious Ursuline Convent. We see how floats are made and delve into Mardi Gras history at Mardi Gras World. Finally, we visit the National World War II Museum's world-class collection of memorabilia.

programme.title: Flagstaff
programme.desc: Get your kicks on Route 66 in Flagstaff, AZ. Discover the enormous Barringer Meteor Crater. Scan the stars for Planet X at Lowell Observatory, and learn the history of the region at the Northern Arizona History Museum. Finally, swing from ponderosa pines at the Flagstaff Extreme Adventure Park.

programme.title: Madagascar - A Multifaceted Land
programme.desc: Madagascar split off from Africa some 150 million years ago. The isolation of being separated from the mainland caused the island's wildlife to develop distinct and unique features. Once a pirate stronghold, today Madagascar has opened itself up to the world, and is revealing its secrets.

programme.title: Laos - Along The Mekong
programme.desc: Isolated from geopolitics for the past 30 years, Laos is now slowly opening to tourism. Its cultures and environment are fragile, and a responsible form of tourism could preserve its past and character. From fishing villages to the forests of northern Laos, meet the people that protect their land.

programme.title: From Peru to Tanzania
programme.desc: There are places on Earth worthy of absolute preservation and protection for all future generations. Meet people from Puerto Rico, Maryland, Peru, Tanzania, Slovakia, and Cambodia who all share an abiding belief in a sacred, healthy Earth.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Edmonton, Canada
programme.desc: In the second part of her tour of Alberta, Canada, you and Donna will discover fresh cuisine at the local farmer's market and explore some of the region’s crafts. You will also go snowshoeing and learn how to ski.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Longyearbyen
programme.desc: Only 650 miles from the North Pole, there are three seasons in Longyearbyen: Polar summer, Northern Lights winter, and Sunny winter, and the elemental side of nature is a common factor in all decisions. The crystalline, light-lit hues of the land can remind one that true spirit shines from within.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: The New China
programme.desc: China is a young, vibrant culture that is making things happen in the world that will affect everyone. This "inside look" at China by Geographic Travel filmmaker Dale Johnson explores China's explosive double-digit growth that has made it among the world's leading economies, with extra potential.

programme.title: Tarpan: Repainting an Ancient Picture
programme.desc: The Tarpan roamed in wild herds across Europe for millennia, yet the breed became extinct in the 19th century. Today, international teams have introduced a herd of genetically bred, modern Tarpan to remote mountains of Eastern Europe where they hope the horses can find their wild spirits again.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Down Under: The Wild West of Cooking
programme.desc: Melbourne, Australia boasts hard-living, good-natured, and eccentric lovers of food - Tony's kind of people. In search of the outlaws of food, Tony explores a pasteurization-free cheese factory, and an old-world cured jamon workshop.

programme.title: Singapore: New York in Twenty Years
programme.desc: Tony sets out to find the real Singapore, with its multicultural restaurants and food markets. He samples prescription food dishes, explores the Geyland Serai Market, and rides the clean and efficient local subway.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Kyushu
programme.desc: Explore the island of Kyushu with it's dramatic landscape and hot sands, and discover the essence of Japanese cuisine with Daisuke Utagawa and Rudy Maxa.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Tokyo
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take us to the heart of Japan in Tokyo where culinary geniuses strive for perfection as they prepare everything from sushi to the wasabi.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Hokkaido
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take you to Japan's northern frontier Hokkaido. The hot spring capital of Japan with its many volcanoes, Hokkaido also boosts some of the world greatest ramen, ramen noodles, and legendary whiskey.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 1
programme.desc: Host Rudy Maxa and Washington, D.C. restaurateur and chef Daisuke Utagawa enthusiastically eat their way through Hong Kong, from cheap but authentic, hole-in-the-wall Chinese restaurants to Michelin-starred palaces. Along the way they illustrate the excitement and energy that defines Hong Kong.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 2
programme.desc: Dramatic photography by renowned shooters Karel Bauer and Joe Pontecorvo bring Hong Kong into viewers' homes as never before. Stray from the iconic photo of Hong Kong as a wall of skyscrapers against Victoria Peak with the city's harbor in a foreground and visits the other side of the island.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Washington, DC, restaurateur Daisuke Utagawa and travel journalist Rudy Max deliver viewers directly to Bangkok’s sprawling city temples, its huge flower market, its vibrant klongs (canals), and to its most interesting cuisine, all of which made Bangkok the world’s most-visited city by travelers.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: Wild National Parks
programme.desc: From grizzly bears of Katmai National Park in Alaska to rattlesnakes of Montezuma's Castle in Arizona, answer the call of America's wildest national parks. By land, sea, and sky, get up close to creatures of all shapes and sizes. Dedicated park workers reveal what it takes to nurture nature.

programme.title: The Mohawk Trail Across New England
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America’s richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: The Iron Curtain Trail
programme.desc: For almost half a century, Europe was demonstrably divided into East and West by the "Iron Curtain,” an imaginary, yet strongly re-enforced, barrier separating Europe that stretched between the Barents and Black Seas. For 40 years, the Iron Curtain was a potent symbol of division between people.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Salt Lake City
programme.desc: Westward ho! We settle in Salt Lake City, where we learn about Brigham Young's settlement of the Utah territory and his monument at This is the Place Park. Then we dig in the dirt to find hundreds of perfectly preserved dinosaurs at the Utah Natural History museum.

programme.title: Albany/Saratoga Springs
programme.desc: Take the Albany capital tour and learn about five former N.Y. governors who became U.S. Presidents. Board the U.S.S. Slater and see how America defended its fleet against German U-boats in World War II. Then, sample the mineral water in Saratoga Springs and bet the farm at the thoroughbred raceway.

programme.title: Egypt - Water And Sand
programme.desc: Siwa is an island-oasis of fire-torched skies in the middle of the Egyptian desert where The Great Sand Sea comes to rest at the foot of an oasis of date palms. Bordered by two lakes of turquoise blue, travelers find themselves at an oasis that is authentically North African.

programme.title: Dominican Republic - Caribbean Treasure
programme.desc: Explore the lesser-known jungles, mountains, and lakes of the Dominican Republic, catch a glimpse of the fascinating history of the Tainos Indians, and listen to the electrifying steps and sounds of merengue dance and salsa music on this Caribbean treasure.

programme.title: From Guatemala to the Congo
programme.desc: Stewardship of the land is a central part of the human condition. Unfortunately, in some cases, so is greed. Meet people from California, Congo, India, Australia, Guatemala, and Slovenia whose spirit matches their intent to live healthily.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: France's Normandy
programme.desc: From a dramatic coast to rural pastures, this sweet section of France abounds with apple orchards, enchanting villages, stunning abbeys, and sparkling seaports. We base in the lovely seaside town Honfleur. At Giverny, and in the museums in Rouen and Honfleur, we discover the birth of Impressionism.

programme.title: Medieval Europe
programme.desc: The medieval world is one of the big draws of European Travel. Moody ruins, "tippy" towers, cobbled streets, sparkling mosaics, monasteries, castles, and cathedrals form the core of many a tourist's dreams. In this episode, we make sense out of a fascinating 1,000 years of history.

programme.title: Santa Barbara, California
programme.desc: Follow Donna to Santa Barbara, California, the “American Rivera,” and learn how to surf. Also, stay in an award-winning resort, and enjoy a dinner at restaurant that only uses organic local ingredients.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: St. Augustine
programme.desc: First, we will take a sip from the distinctively tasting Fountain of Youth. Then we will touch the coquina walls of the undefeated Castillo San Marcos. Next, separate pirate truth from pirate myth at the appropriately named, Pirate Museum, and cure what ails us at the oldest General Store.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: Los Angeles, My Own Heart of Darkness
programme.desc: Los Angeles, CA: New York chef, Anthony Bourdain, descends into the culinary underbelly of his metropolitan nemesis, Los Angeles, where he experiences the trials of celebrity fame and the joys of West Coast cuisine.

programme.title: The French Laundry Experience
programme.desc: Napa, CA: Marooned in San Francisco, Tony tastes local shellfish and durian ice cream before embarking on a pilgrimage to experience the genius of Thomas Keller, chef and owner of The French Laundry.

programme.title: La Paz
programme.desc: Amid the dizzying heights of the Andes Mountains sits Laz Paz, Bolivia. The Mirandas, the friendly family Alexandra will be staying with, introduces her to elements of Bolivian culture that they keep close to their hearts. Also, meet famous Bolivian chola Glenda Yanez.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Gold Coast Australia
programme.desc: If you like sun, surf, sand, and a laid-back lifestyle then join Laura on Australia's Gold Coast. Travel into the thick of the Queensland Rainforest, and visit the home of the largest collection of Australian native animals in the Carrumbin Wildlife Sanctuary.

programme.title: Sicily
programme.desc: Begin on the east coast in Taormina. Laura then takes us to some of Sicily's highlight cities, Palermo and Randazzo. How about a visit to Agrigento, or to the divinely inspired Cathedral Monreale? We will also visit Mt. Etna, an active volcano.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Begin with a tour down the Grand Canal, "the finest street in the world." Next, the pedestrian streets around the Rialto Bridge are lined with shops, and St. Mark's Basilica is one of the oldest and most beautiful Byzantine cathedrals in all of Europe.

programme.title: Oahu, Hawaii
programme.desc: Have a blast with Laura on this Hawaiian voyage as you explore sensational surf and beaches, unique Hawaiian culture and food, and climb volcanic mountains. Join Laura as she visits historic landmarks, such as the Iolani Palace and the Bishop Museum.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: S7E6 - Paris: Regal and Intimate
programme.desc: In Paris, we'll cruise the Seine River, pay a visit to Napoleon’s tomb, and take in the majestic Louvre. Then we'll shop in a village-like neighborhood, attend church in a pipe organ loft, and celebrate Bastille Day.

programme.title: Life or Death
programme.desc: Pilot Luke Hickerson transports dangerous chemicals from Barrow to the remote village of Atqasuk. Then the cold and dark winter claims its first casualty and Jim must make arrangements to transport the casket.

programme.title: America's Treasures: National Parks
programme.desc: A cinematic journey through the awe-inspiring landscapes, historic sites and untamed wilderness of America's most legendary outdoor playgrounds.

programme.title: United States of Sports
programme.desc: Copa90’s Eli and Timbsy and Love Island’s Josh Denzel go on a once-in-a-lifetime road trip. Then, the guys hit the Midwest for an unforgettable road trip through Detroit, Chicago and Cincinnati.

programme.title: Beef Lamb Pig
programme.desc: Guy hunts down all kinds of meaty favorites from cottage pie to Asian-barbeque in Kentucky and North Carolina.

programme.title: Big Food Small Towns
programme.desc: Guy stops in small towns to dig in to big-time eats. In Raymond, NH, a butchery cranks out scratch-made corn dogs. In Rocky Hill, NJ, a 1700s inn turned gastropub dishes out a tomato twist on burgers and a spin on disco fries.

programme.title: Mega Mouthfuls
programme.desc: Guy unhinges his jaw for some mega-mouthful meals. In Louisville, KY, a funky seafood spot piles their specialties on top of waffles, and in Portland, OR, a killer barbecue food truck stacks a fully-loaded "shabamwich."

programme.title: Burgers Buns Bagels
programme.desc: This trip, Guy's picking up everything from burgers to buns to bagels. In Portsmouth, NH, a deli serves up lamb burgers and righteous ribs. In Los Angeles, a Koreatown favorite loads up Asian buns and a unique bacon-corn bar dish.

programme.title: Something in the Water
programme.desc: Chronicles singer-songwriter Steve Azar's endeavor to record his album Down at the Liquor Store at the historic Club Ebony in Indianola, Mississippi with a group of storied musicians.

programme.title: New Mexico: True Stories
programme.desc: New Mexico is a haven for those who seek to follow their own path. See how this adventurous spirit shapes a way of life - from culture to art to cuisine and everything in between.

programme.title: America. The Beautiful.: Columbia River Gorge
programme.desc: Kayaker Rush Sturges rides life-threatening rapids and waterfalls.

programme.title: Roadfood Adventures USA South
programme.desc: Travel the South to find the most colorful roads in the nation and discover delicious food, magnificent scenery, magic moments, and fascinating people all along the way.

programme.title: Meet the Twetos
programme.desc: In the frigid Alaskan town of Unalakleet, the Twetos battle the arctic elements to transport supplies to some of the most inaccessible areas on the planet.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - Bluefin Tuna and Yellowtail Fishing on the El Dorado
programme.desc: Shea McIntee and the crew take a two and a half-day trip on one of our all-time favorite charter boats, the El Dorado, out of Long Beach Sportfishing. We fish on San Clemente Island and venture offshore in search of tuna.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Like Father, Like Son
programme.desc: It’s a family vacation far off the grid as the Dorsey family visit a remote fishing and hunting camp in Saskatchewan. While fishing for giant pike and lake trout they are on the lookout for the area's black bear.

programme.title: Flint Oak Upland
programme.desc: Join Jeff Fuller, along with his sons, Clayton and Callahan, and the dogs of Soggy Acres Retrievers as they travel to Flint Oak Hunting Resort in Kansas for an upland hunt to remember.

programme.title: Before We Sink
programme.desc: The Brigade must contend with a crack in their voyageur canoe in preparation for an epic lake crossing and the most dangerous stretch of rapids. With time a constant pressure and the threat of failure looming, a storm threatens to freeze one of the brigade members. The team receives a surprise from home.

programme.title: Feral Sheep Hunting in Argentina
programme.desc: Jim heads the Argentina to go after some of the cool Barnyard sheep species.

programme.title: Number One Client
programme.desc: Despite his busy schedule, Tom never misses an opportunity to take Jacque on a hunt.

programme.title: Good Times and Good Bulls
programme.desc: Bowhunter's Mike Carney and friends chase bugling bull elk at Cross Mountain Ranch in northwestern Colorado.

programme.title: Texas Bone-Collecting
programme.desc: Stan Potts is headed to south Texas to collect bone at the Partidas Ranch with his buddy Michael Waddell, Dr. Deer shares the advantages of fire in mangement in your management plan, Mr. Shelton talks in-season archery practice and Jeremy Moore delivers part two of a three part series on shed dogs.

programme.title: Super Grouper
programme.desc: Chef Scott Leysath got a ton of grouper from his buddy, Tommy Gomes, and he’s cooking it up 3 different ways. Joining him on the show are Susie Jimenez, Stacy Lyn Harris, Brad Fenson, Cee Dub, and Buddy T.

programme.title: The Reluctant Bottom Feeder
programme.desc: Derek traverses Wisconsin for backbreaking labor on the Mississippi River, and a backbreaking fun at a hog wrestling tournament. Featuring Jeff Ritter.

programme.title: Offshore Gulf Grouper
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Seth Hayes for some incredible offshore gag grouper action off the coast of Ft.Myers.

programme.title: Backwater Series in the Everglades
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Donnie Kish in search of redfish and the first place trophy.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 2
programme.desc: It’s Day 2 of the Golden Fly Tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob is fishing tournament champion Andy Mill and Bou is fishing his friend Paul Nute.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 3
programme.desc: It’s Day 3 of the Golden Fly tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob and Andy Mill have had a productive week, but will need a strong finish to win the event.

programme.title: Young Salt, Old Spirit
programme.desc: Armed with the skills of generations past, rough and tumble New Englanders teach the SFTV crew how to catch the region's sporty summertime species.

programme.title: Atlantic Gladiators
programme.desc: New England pelagics like swordfish and bluefin tuna bring more than sport. It's a heavyweight, high octane battle, and the angler is the underdog.

programme.title: Catch Me If You Can
programme.desc: Three days, five release flags, 400 photos: the SFTV crew and Marlin magazine join forces to chase blue marlin and sailfish at Panama's Tropic Star Lodge.

programme.title: Jacks Be Roiling
